# ProjectFlo — Feature README Convention

- Every backend module folder and frontend feature folder must contain a `README.md` as the single source of domain knowledge for that feature.
- Required sections:
  - What this module does (1 paragraph)
  - Key files table (file → purpose)
  - Business rules / invariants (bullets)
  - Related modules (backend + frontend + reference docs)
- Keep READMEs under ~80 lines; link out to deeper reference docs instead of duplicating them.
- Update the README in the same change/PR as any code change that alters business rules, key files, API routes/transport policy, or cross-module relationships.
- READMEs should not duplicate structural rules from instruction files; they document local invariants, ownership, and file inventory.

